I"Z<p>The anxiety response is kept going when you avoid your feelings through escaping to your mind (rumination).</p>

<p>Self compassion involves bringing your awareness to your discomfort and distress and understanding that your pain and suffering is a normal part of being human.</p>

<p>By bringing an attitude of care and acceptance towards yourself, you can focus our energy away from your worries and concerns, towards a dedicated attempt to reassure and support yourself.</p>

<p>By turning towards your feelings, instead of resisting them, you can begin to self soothe and calm your anxiety.</p>
